# Next.js: Use proxy.ts only (no middleware.ts)

In Next.js 16+, the `middleware.ts` file convention is **deprecated**. Use **`proxy.ts`** only.

- **Do not create** `src/middleware.ts`. The build will fail if both `middleware.ts` and `proxy.ts` exist.
- **Add all request-handling logic** (CORS, cookies, headers, rate limiting, etc.) in `src/proxy.ts`.
- The proxy runs at the edge in front of the app; export a default request handler and optionally `config.matcher`.

If you need new behavior (e.g. headers, cookies, redirects), edit `src/proxy.ts` only.
